---
import BaseLayout, { type JsonLdGraph } from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { ROSE_PERSON_SCHEMA } from "../lib/seo.ts";

const jsonLd: JsonLdGraph[] = [ROSE_PERSON_SCHEMA];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About letmepost.dev: solo, open source, built in public"
  description="letmepost.dev is built by Rose Kamal Love (ex-GrooveHQ, Kroto). Apache 2.0, solo-dev shop, transparent about what works and what doesn't."
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <header class="wrap page-head">
    <p class="crumb"><a href="/">letmepost</a> / about</p>
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1 class="cl-h1" style="max-width: 16ch;">One operator. One inbox. <span class="acc">Open source.</span></h1>
    <p class="sub" style="max-width: 58ch;">
      letmepost.dev is a solo-dev shop building the social media publishing API the
      existing ones aren't. No funding round, no growth team, no per-profile billing tax.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="wrap sec tight">
    <p class="kicker">Who</p>
    <h2 class="cl-h2">Rose Kamal Love.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        Founder. Solo. Previously engineering at <b>GrooveHQ</b> and <b>Kroto</b>.
        I've shipped customer-facing software for ten years and built two products that
        grew through developer trust, not ad spend. letmepost.dev is the third.
      </p>
      <p>
        Find me on <a href="https://github.com/rosekamallove">GitHub</a>,
        <a href="https://x.com/rosekamallove">X</a>, and
        <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/rosekamallove.dev">Bluesky</a>. Email
        <a href="mailto:rose@letmepost.dev">rose@letmepost.dev</a> reaches me directly,
        usually inside 24h on weekdays.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap sec divider">
    <p class="kicker">Why this</p>
    <h2 class="cl-h2">Loud failure, per-org billing, pinned versions.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        Every existing social media API has the same shape: per-profile billing that
        punishes scale, silent failure modes that punish debugging, and a six-month
        half-life on platform integrations because nobody pins API versions.
      </p>
      <p>
        letmepost.dev is the version where failure is loud, billing is per-org, version
        pinning is the contract, and the entire stack is Apache 2.0. The hosted SaaS
        runs the exact image you can self-host. No open-core trick.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap sec divider">
    <p class="kicker">How we work</p>
    <h2 class="cl-h2">Build in public, honest status.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <ul>
        <li><b>Build in public.</b> Roadmap, status, and platform-review state live on the marketing pages. The <a href="/status">status page</a> is the same metrics dashboard we look at.</li>
        <li><b>Honest status.</b> Bluesky, X, and Pinterest are live end-to-end. Instagram, Facebook, Threads, and LinkedIn are in platform review; TikTok is in App Review. We never mark a platform "available" before it is.</li>
        <li><b>No sales call required.</b> Free tier, public pricing, Stripe Checkout. Email us if Business+ doesn't cover what you need, but you don't have to.</li>
        <li><b>Open source from day one.</b> <a href="https://github.com/letmepost/letmepost.dev">github.com/letmepost</a>. Apache 2.0. Self-host the same image that runs the hosted SaaS.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap">
    <div class="final">
      <h2>Build on it, or read the source.</h2>
      <p>Open an issue, send a PR, or just send your first post. We build in the open.</p>
      <div class="ctas">
        <a class="btn pri lg" href="https://dashboard.letmepost.dev">Start free →</a>
        <a class="btn ghost lg" href="https://github.com/letmepost/letmepost.dev">View source ↗</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
